\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie pedaled steadily through the streets of Osthaven, the hum of the town buzzing around him. The salty breeze had thinned, replaced by the scent of fresh bread, spices, and something sweet roasting over an open flame. His stomach reminded him, with a low grumble, that breakfast had been hurried.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He slowed to a stop near a familiar stall, the one that sold honeyed almonds and sesame biscuits. The sight alone pulled him back to old routines\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 grabbing a bag for himself, an extra for Markus. It had been a while, but some habits never quite faded.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 After paying the vendor, he stepped back toward his bicycle, ready to sling the bag over the handlebars\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 when something caught his eye.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A building stood across the street, its architecture different from the others around it. Age clung to its stone walls, yet the towering columns bore intricate carvings, their shapes unmistakably Elvish. Time had weathered them, but their elegance remained, a relic of a bygone era.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Above the heavy wooden doors, an emblem was set in iron: an owl, perched upon a scroll, wings tucked close. Beneath it, carved into the worn brass plaque, were two simple words.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b1\i0 Sage Institute.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie stared, something stirring in his chest. He hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t noticed it before\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 maybe he had never cared to look. But now, standing there, it felt like the building was watching him back.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eyes tracing the contours of the emblem, }{\f3\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie lingered a moment longer, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 the owl\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s unblinking gaze seeming almost knowing. The Sage Institute. He knew nothing about it\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 had never needed to\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 but something about it gnawed at the edges of his mind. A curiosity, fleeting yet persistent.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 With a breath, he shook it off, tucking the bag of snacks securely inside his satchel before turning back to his bicycle. The world outside his thoughts rushed back in\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the chatter of merchants, the rhythmic clatter of hooves on cobblestones, the occasional call of dockworkers hauling cargo.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He swung a leg over the bike and pushed off, weaving through the streets of Osthaven with practiced ease. The town passed him by in a blur of nostalgia and familiarity, but his mind remained half elsewhere, lingering on the building, on the emblem, on the feeling.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The distant chime of a bell tower reminded him of the time. He wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t in a hurry, but he didn\u8217\'92t want to miss the next ferry back to Weshaven either.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 By the time he reached the harbor, the ferry was already boarding. He rolled his bicycle up the gangway, found a quiet spot near the railing, and exhaled, letting the sea breeze wash over him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Back to Weshaven. Back to his routines.}
